---
title: Beef & Veggie Bibimbap with Carrots & Pickled Scallions
description: This dish takes its name from the Korean word for mixing rice. Which is exactly what you’re meant to do after serving it: Put your rice in a bowl, add the toppings, and mix it all together so that those flavors and textures combine in a glorious mishmash. There are plenty of flavors and textures going on here, too, like sweet carrot, tender zucchini, and pork tossed with garlic, ginger, and soy sauce.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/621fa9df74792001df6bfa90-bd746f7d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/beef-veggie-bibimbap-621fa9df74792001df6bfa90-6effdaa1.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 810 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 84 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1240 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/beef-veggie-bibimbap-621fa9df74792001df6bfa90
course: main course
---

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and peel @Carrots{6%oz}. Using a #peeler{}, shave carrots lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core; discard core. Trim and halve @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Peel and mince @Ginger{1%thumb} and @Garlic{1%clove}.

== Pickled Scallions ==

In a small #bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sesame Oil{1%tablespoon}, half the @Soy Sauce{2%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), @Sugar{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and up to half the @Sriracha{2%teaspoon} to taste. Stir until sugar has dissolved.

== Veggies ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add carrots; season with @salt and @pepper. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Add another drizzle of oil to pan. Add zucchini; season with @salt and @pepper. Cook until browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside with carrots.

== Beef ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Beef{10%oz}, ginger, and garlic. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until pork is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add remaining soy sauce and cook, stirring, until liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt and @pepper.

> Swap in beef for pork if desired.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with @salt and @pepper; divide between #bowls{}.

Arrange pork and veggies on top. Top with pickled scallion whites (and pickling liquid). Drizzle with sauce and remaining Sriracha to taste. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.